  "notes": "Western Armenian (Արեւմտահայերէն) — the standard form of Modern Armenian of the Ottoman/diaspora tradition, written in the Armenian alphabet using classical (Mesropian) spelling. Its defining feature is the consonant shift relative to Eastern Armenian: the classical voiced series բ գ դ ձ ջ is read as aspirated voiceless /pʰ kʰ tʰ tsʰ tʃʰ/, while the classical voiceless series պ կ տ ծ ճ is read as voiced /b ɡ d dz dʒ/. Digraph ⟨ու⟩ = /u/; ⟨և⟩ = /ɛv/ (word-initially /jɛv/). Word-initial ⟨ե⟩ is /jɛ/ and word-initial ⟨ո⟩ is /vɔ/. ⟨ն⟩ is [ŋ] before velars. Stress is on the final syllable.",
